= Devices
/ Calligraphic Display Devices: Draw polygons and line segments directly. The image is a regular grid of samples.
Examples: Plotters, Laser light projection

/ Raster Display Devices: Each sample is a pixel. ("Picture element"). Rendering requires rasterization to determine a sampled representation of geometric primitives.

== Monitor
=== CRT
/ Raster Cathode Ray Tubes (CRT): Electron beam scanned in regular pattern of horizontal scanlines. 

/ Raster images: Are stored in a frame buffer
Intensity of electron beam modifies the pixel value.
/ Colour CRTS: 3 different electron guns shoot into coloured filters
/ Shadow masks: Allow each gun to irradiate only its corresponding colour phosphor dots

=== LCD
/ Liquid Crystal Display (LCD): Allows random access to cells. These contain liquid crystal molecules that can align when charged. Unaligned molecules twist light. Polarizing filters only allows light through unaligned molecules. 